Let me start off by saying you both are doing GREAT! parenting doesn’t come with a handbook , you learn as you go. No matter if this is your 1st or 5th child. Every baby is different .

To me this sounds like colic 😢 my 1st born son was on formula GENTLEASE since he didn’t latch right on breastfeeding . My 2nd baby breastfed for 1month straight ! (It’s a lot of work , so I’m proud of myself lol) then I struggled to produce again. So we put him on formula. But he didn’t do well with GENTLEASE like my 1st born, but even towards the end of my breastfeeding time , we realized some foods I was eating may upset my sons tummy. I had to stop eating spicy foods, etc. So we did the same you guys did. Took him to the ER, found out he had colic & the soy prosobee formula helped his little tummy !

Prayers for you two as you learn this new parenthood journey! You got this! In Jesus name 🙏🏽❤️! And prayers to your baby girl! For her little tummy & that she gets more peaceful rest ! ❤️❤️🙏🏽

snippet.textDisplay: I noticed you guys went to Kaiser. Normally they give immediate priority to infants in the ER because they have a weaker immune system. Working in the medical field, if you god forbid ever have to go back to the ER, you can demand a Pediatrician. There is always one on call. I think shes either has Colic or because your breastfeeding, something you ate does not agree with Soul. I would start keeping track of EVERYTHING you eat and see the patterns if she gets like that. Sometimes it can be spicy food or lots of dairy can upset their tummy. If you sit her on your leg, put one hand to support her underneath her neck, lean her forward a little bit and pat and rub her back, that can help ease out any gas or indigestion she may have. Hope this helps

snippet.textDisplay: I happened upon this video by total accident. Subscribed to your page after watching this video. Let’s start by saying she is absolutely beautiful and congratulations! I have 3 children of my own, which of the first child I ever had, my daughter, had colic. She definitely seems to have the same symptoms that my daughter had. Please don’t take anything I say in any way, the wrong way. I am just throwing this out there because I wish I would’ve known what I know now when I was a new mom. My daughter cried all.the.time. If she was awake. The only way she’d sleep is if I held her. And even then sometimes she’d wake up, screaming out of the blue. Grunting, straining, she’d cry like someone had hit her. I was so so stressed out. I took her to the hospital at least 10 times. I tried gripe water, nothing helped. She finally grew out of it around 4 months old but I swear I was so upset because those were the longest 4 months of my life and I felt like I was always more worried rather than being able to spend quality time and enjoy her. Little did I know she had colic. As I got older, and had more kids I knew what to expect and how to fix it. I know you are breast feeding, but with my last and final baby, he showed signs of colic early on. I attempted to breast feed and it didn’t work for me. I decided on my own that I was going to switch his formula. I switched him to Similac Alimentum, and then was told our local WIC wouldn’t pay for it unless there was a reason. I explained to his pediatrician that he showed signs of colic so I tried to nip it in the butt. She then suggested soy, which in turn made him worse and he ended up with bloody stools, finally he was put on Nutramigen which is hypoallergenic formula, as finding out he had a cows milk protein allergy. I know it’s not the same, but I’ve also heard of babies having colic with the breast milk too. It saved him, he no longer had issues at all. He was happy, healthy, and boy did he put down some formula from then on out. I fed him on demand, I didn’t go by the standards. I wish I had known to do this with my daughter. To save her, and I, some long sleepless and worrisome nights. Just know you two are doing an amazing job being parents as well. That’s just from my own experience! I had tried gripe water and even mylicon gas drops for my little girl and neither helped her. Watching this just brought me back to that time in my life where I was at a loss of what to do for her.
